Not really. It's about getting the sound you want.

The only advice you do need is not to play too loud on stage. The sound from the
amps will either spill into every mic and destroy any chance of a decent mix.or
simply overwhelm the PA with their raw SPL and mess things up that way. OR the
sound engineer will compensate with the PA level and deafen everyone. Bad news
whichever way it goes.

Turn DOWN.

Graham
