A good place to look is the actual vocal mic and it's spec's.  Getting a
modern mic (like the Audix om5-7) that you have to 'eat' to sing on will
pick up less drums and gtr amp. Isolation is the key to lower stage volume,
and if you can't do it with space, do it with smart mic positioning, monitor
and amp placement.  It's pretty hard to talk about stage dynamics as a
player if the stage vol is already loud before you even start playing gtr
due to the wedges.  Another thing is to not put anything in your wedge that
you can already hear from elsewhere. That could substantially reduce the
volume just by having less duplication of sound.

